            "content": {
                "raw": "The new version is an improvement, but we still have two nested, mutually exclusive `if` statements, and all of them perform early returns.  This is confusing to the reader, particularly since the reader will already be reading through the logic of the conditionals.  Here is what I think it should look like:\n\n\n```\n#!python\ndef _ThermalEnergy(field, data):\n    if data.pf[\"HydroMethod\"] == 2:\n        return data[\"TotalEnergy\"]\n    elif data.pf[\"DualEnergyFormalism\"]:\n        return data[\"GasEnergy\"]\n    elif data.pf[\"HydroMethod\"] in (4,6):\n        return data[\"TotalEnergy\"] - 0.5*(\n             data[\"x-velocity\"]**2.0\n           + data[\"y-velocity\"]**2.0\n           + data[\"z-velocity\"]**2.0 ) - \\\n           data[\"MagneticPressure\"]\n    return data[\"TotalEnergy\"] - 0.5*(\n             data[\"x-velocity\"]**2.0\n           + data[\"y-velocity\"]**2.0\n           + data[\"z-velocity\"]**2.0 )\n```",
                "html": "<p>The new version is an improvement, but we still have two nested, mutually exclusive <code>if</code> statements, and all of them perform early returns.  This is confusing to the reader, particularly since the reader will already be reading through the logic of the conditionals.  Here is what I think it should look like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">_ThermalEnergy</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">field</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pf</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;HydroMethod&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;TotalEnergy&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">elif</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pf</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;DualEnergyFormalism&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;GasEnergy&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">elif</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pf</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;HydroMethod&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span> <span class=\"ow\">in</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">6</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;TotalEnergy&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">-</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.5</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n             <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;x-velocity&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">**</span><span class=\"mf\">2.0</span>\n           <span class=\"o\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;y-velocity&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">**</span><span class=\"mf\">2.0</span>\n           <span class=\"o\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;z-velocity&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">**</span><span class=\"mf\">2.0</span> <span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">-</span> \\\n           <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;MagneticPressure&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;TotalEnergy&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">-</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.5</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n             <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;x-velocity&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">**</span><span class=\"mf\">2.0</span>\n           <span class=\"o\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;y-velocity&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">**</span><span class=\"mf\">2.0</span>\n           <span class=\"o\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;z-velocity&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">**</span><span class=\"mf\">2.0</span> <span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre></div>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
